CatDescriptText: Cutline of image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper December 8, 1945, pg. 24, reads: "Hot Threesome - Dole Dicken's Trio, now playing at the Oasis, came to Pittsburgh from New York.  Dickens, bass, formerly played with the Fiddle More Four; Dickie Thompson is the blues singer, and Teddy Brannon formerly played with Benny Carter's ork. - Harris Photo."
TitMainTitle: Dole Dickens' Trio with Dickens on bass, Teddy Brannon, and Dickie Thompson posed on stage under tent decoration, possibly Oasis Club
